<paragraph id="3340217A40305F1BFCC8FE9E4BD9392A" blockId="39.[826,1441,276,328]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCC8FE9E4CDC394B" box="[826,952,276,297]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name ‘ 
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFBB4FE9E4BD7394B" box="[1094,1203,276,297]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">puyarum’</emphasis>
is descriptive of the colloquial name of the host plant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40305F1BFCC8FEEE4BA73BDD" blockId="39.[826,1442,355,1144]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCC8FEEE4BF4391B" box="[826,1168,355,377]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFBF8FEE94BF4391B" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1034,1168,355,377]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">C. puyarum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to the 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFA91FEE94CFF39F5" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFA91FEE94CFF39F5" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in size and general appearance. However 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFC84FE2B4C9F39D4" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[886,1019,417,438]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFC84FE2B4C9F39D4" box="[886,1019,417,438]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have a flattened face and the tubercle is well produced. In comparison with other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFC8CFE544B393996" box="[894,1117,478,500]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFC8CFE544B663991" box="[894,1026,478,499]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Copestylum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFB9BFE544B8A3991" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1129,1262,478,499]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFB9BFE544B8A3991" box="[1129,1262,478,499]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFCA5FE774B6C3A73" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[855,1032,508,530]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnigaster">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCA5FE774B6C3A73" box="[855,1032,508,530]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. brunnigaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being a large species with a narrow dusted face, thoracic pile of mixed size, prescutellar bristles, and with an extensively yellow abdomen. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFCC8FDD34CA43A0C" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,960,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCC8FDD34CA43A0C" box="[826,960,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFBACFDD34A6B3A0F" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[1118,1295,600,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnigaster">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFBACFDD34A6B3A0F" box="[1118,1295,600,622]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. brunnigaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a shorter face with black vittae, a broader band of apical black setae on tergite 2, about a quarter the length of the tergite, and well developed prescutellar bristles. The larva and puparium of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFB9DFD594B913A8B" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1135,1269,723,745]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFB9DFD594B913A8B" box="[1135,1269,723,745]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFC91FD784CB43B65" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[867,976,754,775]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="louisae">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFC91FD784CB43B65" box="[867,976,754,775]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. louisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among those considered here. They both share a thorax broader than the abdomen, an elongate anal segment, and sensilla 5–8 of abdominal segments 5–7 on elongate fleshy projections. The ridge-shaped as opposed to spherical prolegs, and lappets covered in stout as opposed to fine setae, distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFC73FC204B633BDD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[897,1031,938,959]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFC73FC204B633BDD" box="[897,1031,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFBBFFC204BD83BDD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1101,1212,938,959]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="louisae">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFBBFFC204BD83BDD" box="[1101,1212,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">C. louisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40305F1BFCA1FC434C153C1A" blockId="39.[826,1442,355,1144]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
A larva similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFBB0FC434BCE3BBC" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1090,1194,969,990]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFBB0FC434BCE3BBC" box="[1090,1194,969,990]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found, but not reared, in the decaying bases of puya plants at the base of Mount Cotapaxi, near Quito, 
<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA40305F1BFAE9FB8C4A1E3C7E" box="[1307,1402,1030,1052]" name="Ecuador" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
in 
<date id="474107BA40305F1BFCC8FBAF4CB73C58" box="[826,979,1061,1082]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" value="2000-08">August 2000</date>
. This larva can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFCC8FBCE4CC63C3B" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,930,1092,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puyarum">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCC8FBCE4CC63C3B" box="[826,930,1092,1113]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">puyarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the vestiture, which is only about half as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40305F1BFCC8FB1A4AC63D5D" blockId="39.[826,1442,1168,1343]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840305F1BFCC8FB1A4CF13CC7" box="[826,917,1168,1189]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Biology:</emphasis>
Larvae were collected in wet decaying leaves at the base of dead flower spikes of puya plants (
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940305F1BFCB0FB474C853C81" box="[834,993,1229,1251]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
). Sometimes the level of decay was extensive and pools of water were present. Nonetheless, decay was generally deep down and often underground, and was located only with considerable effort.
</paragraph>
